"```sql\nSELECT c.gender\nFROM client c\nJOIN disp d ON c.client_id = d.client_id\nJOIN account a ON d.account_id = a.account_id\nJOIN district dis ON a.district_id = dis.district_id\nWHERE a.date = (\n    SELECT MIN(a2.date)\n    FROM account a2\n    JOIN disp d2 ON a2.account_id = d2.account_id\n    JOIN client c2 ON d2.client_id = c2.client_id\n    WHERE c2.birth_date = (\n        SELECT MIN(c3.birth_date)\n        FROM client c3\n        JOIN disp d3 ON c3.client_id = d3.client_id\n        JOIN account a3 ON d3.account_id = a3.account_id\n        JOIN district dis3 ON a3.district_id = dis3.district_id\n        WHERE dis3.A11 = (\n            SELECT MAX(dis4.A11)\n            FROM district dis4\n        )\n    )\n)\nAND dis.A11 = (\n    SELECT MAX(dis5.A11)\n    FROM district dis5\n);\n```\n\nThis SQL query finds the gender of the oldest client who opened their account in the branch with the highest average salary. It does this by joining the necessary tables and filtering based on the conditions provided in the question and evidence."